Yesterday:
HTML basics:
1.1 HTML structure: <html>, <head>, <body>.
1.2 Common tags: <h1> to <h6>, <p>, <a>, <img>, <ul>, <ol>, <div>.
1.3 Forms and inputs: <form>, <input>, <button>, <select>.
1.4 Semantic elements: <header>, <footer>, <article>, <section>.

Today:
CSS Basics:
1.1 Selectors: Element, class, ID selectors.
1.2 Box model: Margins, padding, borders.
1.3 Positioning: Static, relative, absolute, fixed.
1.4 Layouts: Flexbox basics (justify-content, align-items).
1.5 Basic styling: Colors, fonts, borders, background images.

Task-
1. Add Styling to Your Day 1 Webpage:
Create an external CSS file and link it to your HTML.
Style the page using the following:
Change background colors for each section (e.g., About Me, Skills).
Use padding and margins to improve spacing between sections.

